parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt retractor can cause the seat belt to lock up or fail to retract, which can lead to accidents or injuries in the event of a crash.
symptoms: The seat belt retractor locks up
the seat belt fails to retract
the seat belt becomes stuck inside the door
the seat belt must be driven over bumps to release
the seat belt stays in the release position.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine head gasket failure can cause coolant to leak into the engine, leading to damage to bearings and potentially causing engine failure, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.
Engine block failure can cause the engine to stall without warning, leading to loss of power steering and potentially causing accidents.
Valve spring failure can cause the engine to rough idle, overheat, and potentially lead to engine failure.
Intermittent engine shutdown can cause the vehicle to shut off without warning, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
Electrical system failure can cause an electrical fire, potentially leading to accidents or injuries.
Vehicle fire can cause accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
